        <section>
            <h2>Introduction to Key Biomarkers</h2>
            <p>
                Systemic inflammation is triggered by the activation of specific signaling molecules known as 
                <span class="tooltip">biomarkers<span class="tooltiptext">Biomarkers are measurable substances in the body that indicate a biological state or condition.</span></span>. 
                These biomarkers are crucial in diagnosing and monitoring inflammatory diseases, infections, and autoimmune conditions. 
                The four key biomarkers that are central to our research include:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>C-reactive Protein (CRP)</li>
                <li>Interleukin-6 (IL-6)</li>
                <li>Tumor Necrosis Factor-alpha (TNF-alpha)</li>
                <li>Interleukin-1 (IL-1)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- CRP Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>1. C-reactive Protein (CRP)</h2>
            <p>
                CRP is an acute-phase protein produced by the liver in response to 
                <span class="tooltip">cytokines<span class="tooltiptext">Cytokines are signaling proteins secreted by cells to regulate immunity and inflammation.</span></span> like IL-6. 
                Its levels rise during systemic inflammation, making it a key marker for identifying inflammatory responses.
            </p>
            <div class="image-container">
                <a href="#" onclick="openLightbox('Images/CRPpathway.png')">
                    <img src="Images/CRPpathway.png" alt="C-reactive Protein Pathway" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;">
                </a>
                <div class="image-caption">
                    <h4>Pathway Overview</h4>
                    <p>This pathway highlights CRP's role in inflammatory responses.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- IL-6 Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>2. Interleukin-6 (IL-6)</h2>
            <p>
                IL-6 is a cytokine that regulates fever and inflammation. It promotes the differentiation of B cells and the production of acute-phase proteins like CRP.
            </p>
            <div class="image-container">
                <a href="#" onclick="openLightbox('Images/IL6pathway.jpg')">
                    <img src="Images/IL6pathway.jpg" alt="Interleukin-6 Pathway" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;">
                </a>
                <div class="image-caption">
                    <h4>Pathway Overview</h4>
                    <p>This pathway highlights the systemic role of IL-6 in inflammation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- TNF-alpha Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>3. Tumor Necrosis Factor-alpha (TNF-alpha)</h2>
            <p>
                TNF-alpha is a central mediator of inflammation, activating pathways like 
                <span class="tooltip">NF-κB<span class="tooltiptext">NF-κB is a protein complex controlling DNA transcription and cytokine production.</span></span> 
                to promote cytokine production and inflammation.
            </p>
            <div class="image-container">
                <a href="#" onclick="openLightbox('Images/TNFpathway.png')">
                    <img src="Images/TNFpathway.png" alt="TNF-alpha Pathway" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;">
                </a>
                <div class="image-caption">
                    <h4>Pathway Overview</h4>
                    <p>This pathway maps TNF-alpha's role in inflammatory diseases.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- IL-1 Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>4. Interleukin-1 (IL-1)</h2>
            <p>
                IL-1 triggers inflammation by recruiting immune cells and promoting other pro-inflammatory cytokines like IL-6 and TNF-alpha. 
                It also causes fever through its action on the hypothalamus.
            </p>
            <div class="image-container">
                <a href="#" onclick="openLightbox('Images/IL1pathway.png')">
                    <img src="Images/IL1pathway.png" alt="Interleukin-1 Pathway" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto;">
                </a>
                <div class="image-caption">
                    <h4>Pathway Overview</h4>
                    <p>This image highlights IL-1's key pathways in inflammation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Common Features Section -->
        <section>
            <h2>Common Features of These Biomarkers</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Inflammatory Response:</strong> All biomarkers play a role in initiating or propagating inflammation.</li>
                <li><strong>Acute-Phase Response:</strong> CRP and cytokines like IL-6 regulate acute-phase proteins.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- References Section -->
        <section id="references">
            <h2>References</h2>
